    <h1>Node pools</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>Each cluster contains a default node pool for application worklo=
ads. This node pool is used if nothing else is specified by an application =
team during deployment. However in certain cases the default node pool migh=
t not be suitable for an application because the underlying nodes (virtual =
machines) do not provide sufficient compute power or memory. In this case a=
n application team can approach the HaCT team to get an additional node poo=
l deployed to the cluster.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">In order to make use of a specific node pool other than the default nod=
e pool define a toleration in your deployment file.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">See:&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://docs.microsoft.com=
/en-us/azure/aks/use-multiple-node-pools#schedule-pods-using-taints-and-tol=
erations" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/aks/use-m=
ultiple-node-pools#schedule-pods-using-taints-and-tolerations</a></span></s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">A sample deployment file is attached here:.</span></span></p>
<p><a href=3D"/sales/download/attachments/44005703/example-toleration.yml?v=
ersion=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1588081460000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-linked-r=
esource-id=3D"44005702" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-reso=
urce-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"example-tole=
ration.yml" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"application/octet-stream" =
data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"44005703" data-linked-resource-contain=
er-version=3D"5">example-toleration.yml</a></p>
<p>In addition to the application node pool the Kubernetes contains a syste=
m node pool that runs internal services of the cluster. This node pool is n=
ot available for application deployments.</p>
